US, US

3
00:00:04.100 --> 00:00:09.340
US, ALL OF US

4
00:00:12.970 --> 00:00:15.770
The end of the dream, the end of the sea

5
00:00:15.770 --> 00:00:17.750
We all have different places we want to go We all have different places we want to go WE ALL HAVE DIFFERENT PLACES WE WANT TO GO

6
00:00:15.790 --> 00:00:18.530
We all have different places we want to go

7
00:00:18.530 --> 00:00:21.310
But to start we've got to show what we're made of

8
00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:25.660
We'll be legends, we're gonna take the world by storm

9
00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:29.250
Sparks are flying, NO LIMITS! This is where it starts

10
00:00:29.250 --> 00:00:30.530
ONE PIECE!!

11
00:00:30.890 --> 00:00:33.510
VORONOI START VORONOI END ALL OF US, I've got a question for you ALL OF US, I've got a question for you

12
00:00:33.510 --> 00:00:37.100
Have you let the world and all its burdens bring your dreams down?

13
00:00:38.740 --> 00:00:45.300
Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much

14
00:00:45.410 --> 00:00:52.030
Still we try, ALL OF US have our own paths we cling to

15
00:00:52.030 --> 00:00:54.620
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you

16
00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:55.150
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

17
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:58.200
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

18
00:00:54.740 --> 00:00:58.050
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

19
00:00:59.890 --> 00:01:02.580
Random clues suddenly fit together

20
00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:06.510
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

21
00:01:06.510 --> 00:01:12.980
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

22
00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:18.680
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

23
00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:21.250
US, US

24
00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:26.360
US, ALL OF US

25
00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:33.490
<b>Miss Buckingham Stussy</b>

26
00:01:36.410 --> 00:01:38.490
I can't wrap my head around this.

27
00:01:47.420 --> 00:01:49.550
So when you don't understand something...

28
00:01:50.380 --> 00:01:52.220
your first instinct is to kill it?

29
00:01:58.470 --> 00:02:00.350
Paper Art: Afterimage!

30
00:02:03.440 --> 00:02:04.440
Oh, you...

31
00:02:08.270 --> 00:02:10.400
You're so wild.

32
00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:12.320
Seastone?!

33
00:02:30.300 --> 00:02:32.260
Y-You damn...!

34
00:02:34.300 --> 00:02:37.180
I know how strong you boys are...

35
00:02:37.550 --> 00:02:40.640
I'm not dumb enough to fight fair against you.

36
00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:44.560
Forgive me, would you?

37
00:02:48.020 --> 00:02:49.230
What?!

38
00:02:49.610 --> 00:02:52.280
Wait a minute! What's going on?!

39
00:02:52.280 --> 00:02:54.950
Why are CP0 agents fighting each other?!

40
00:02:54.950 --> 00:02:57.450
Hey, what's going on?

41
00:02:57.450 --> 00:02:58.660
Did you have a falling out?

42
00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:00.870
This is Stussy.

43
00:03:00.870 --> 00:03:02.080
I put both of them to sleep.

44
00:03:02.080 --> 00:03:02.950
I put both of them to sleep.

45
00:03:03.790 --> 00:03:05.920
She took down Rob Lucci?!

46
00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:07.380
What's going on?!

47
00:03:08.580 --> 00:03:11.380
Even Lucci couldn't have seen it coming.

48
00:03:13.300 --> 00:03:14.840
Oh, wonderful!

49
00:03:14.840 --> 00:03:16.630
Stussy came through!

50
00:03:17.590 --> 00:03:19.680
Help...

51
00:03:19.680 --> 00:03:20.850
York!

52
00:03:20.850 --> 00:03:24.430
Are you all right?! Stay with me! York!

53
00:03:25.520 --> 00:03:27.060
I feel sick...

54
00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:30.110
I can't eat anymore.

55
00:03:30.110 --> 00:03:31.980
Please hurry and wake up!

56
00:03:31.980 --> 00:03:33.440
This is an emergency!

57
00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:35.950
So, who is Stussy?

58
00:03:35.950 --> 00:03:40.910
She's been working as an undercover
agent for us for over twenty years.

59
00:03:40.910 --> 00:03:45.040
What?! You sent a spy
into an intelligence agency?!

60
00:03:45.040 --> 00:03:47.250
That wasn't the original plan...

61
00:03:47.250 --> 00:03:48.920
but it ended up that way.

62
00:03:49.830 --> 00:03:51.290
But, Doctor...

63
00:03:51.670 --> 00:03:54.010
my rank is the same as Lucci's.

64
00:03:54.710 --> 00:03:57.590
I can't override his orders to the seraphim.

65
00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:06.100
There's nothing I can do to stop them.

66
00:04:08.900 --> 00:04:11.480
You've done enough, Stussy!

67
00:04:11.480 --> 00:04:13.440
We're on our way!

68
00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:15.400
We'll stop 'em no matter what!

69
00:04:22.330 --> 00:04:27.750
We gotta stop those kids,
or everyone will get buried in rubble!

70
00:04:27.750 --> 00:04:28.790
Indeed!

71
00:04:28.790 --> 00:04:30.330
But is it just me...

72
00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:33.590
or do those kids look familiar?

73
00:04:33.590 --> 00:04:35.590
Yeah, they do.

74
00:04:35.590 --> 00:04:36.550
Especially...

75
00:04:37.420 --> 00:04:39.130
him.

76
00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:54.480
Consarnit!

77
00:04:54.480 --> 00:04:57.360
They're making a mess of our lab!

78
00:04:57.360 --> 00:04:59.490
Sure made it easier to get out, though...

79
00:04:59.490 --> 00:05:01.320
I'm going first!

80
00:05:01.320 --> 00:05:02.870
No!

81
00:05:02.870 --> 00:05:05.450
That's a bad idea!

82
00:05:07.290 --> 00:05:09.160
Alright! I'm out!

83
00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:12.290
Hey!

84
00:05:12.670 --> 00:05:14.630
Seraphim!

85
00:05:14.630 --> 00:05:17.300
Here's an order!

86
00:05:55.250 --> 00:05:57.090
Looking closer...

87
00:05:58.550 --> 00:06:01.630
you're a little more human than he is.

88
00:06:06.430 --> 00:06:09.020
What the hell are you, kid?!

89
00:06:19.030 --> 00:06:21.780
That gave me such a scare!

90
00:06:21.780 --> 00:06:23.360
Are you okay, Lilith?!

91
00:06:23.360 --> 00:06:25.700
All right! I've got it from here!

92
00:06:26.660 --> 00:06:28.780
Seraphim!

93
00:06:28.780 --> 00:06:32.080
Stand...

94
00:06:32.830 --> 00:06:35.540
down!

95
00:06:39.090 --> 00:06:41.710
Edison!

96
00:06:49.970 --> 00:06:51.850
Just in time!

97
00:06:51.850 --> 00:06:53.310
You're...

98
00:06:54.940 --> 00:06:55.980
Edison!

99
00:06:57.940 --> 00:06:59.070
Hey...

100
00:06:59.070 --> 00:07:00.780
Don't tell me...

101
00:07:09.240 --> 00:07:10.280
Dear Lilith.

102
00:07:10.830 --> 00:07:12.410
Are you worrying about...

103
00:07:12.410 --> 00:07:13.870
this guy?

104
00:07:16.750 --> 00:07:18.960
Edison!

105
00:07:18.960 --> 00:07:20.750
That was close!

106
00:07:20.750 --> 00:07:24.220
I thought my goose was cooked!

107
00:07:39.610 --> 00:07:42.610
It would seem that
the doppelgangers have stopped.

108
00:07:44.110 --> 00:07:46.860
Hey! What the hell are they?!

109
00:07:47.490 --> 00:07:48.860
What's going on?!

110
00:07:49.950 --> 00:07:51.450
Don't worry!

111
00:07:51.450 --> 00:07:54.200
They're just my darling little warriors!

112
00:07:54.200 --> 00:07:56.460
They won't be bothering us anymore!

113
00:07:56.460 --> 00:08:00.330
Since our rank of authority
is higher than CPO's,

114
00:08:00.330 --> 00:08:03.170
we overwrote their commands
to the seraphim.

115
00:08:06.300 --> 00:08:09.680
Your mossy head couldn't
possibly comprehend it.

116
00:08:10.760 --> 00:08:13.350
You're pissing me off, dumbass cook!

117
00:08:13.350 --> 00:08:14.720
Zoro-phim, stand down!

118
00:08:14.720 --> 00:08:16.680
Don't treat me like a seraphim!

119
00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:17.980
Green-aphim, deactivate!

120
00:08:17.980 --> 00:08:19.850
Shut up, swirly-phim!

121
00:08:18.690 --> 00:08:21.690
So, what should we do now?

122
00:08:19.850 --> 00:08:21.690
I'll kill you, where-aphim!

123
00:08:21.690 --> 00:08:25.110
We've been entrusted
with an important mission.

124
00:08:25.610 --> 00:08:30.610
We've got to work together
to help Vegapunk off the island!

125
00:08:31.370 --> 00:08:33.580
You're full of energy!

126
00:08:33.950 --> 00:08:37.250
Super!

127
00:08:38.160 --> 00:08:39.210
Shaka.

128
00:08:41.630 --> 00:08:45.170
I put Lucci and Kaku in seastone cuffs.

129
00:08:45.170 --> 00:08:46.840
Thank you, Stussy.

130
00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:52.180
We're going to leave this island
on the Straw Hats' ship.

131
00:08:52.180 --> 00:08:53.430
Come with us.

132
00:08:53.430 --> 00:08:54.810
Roger.

133
00:08:54.810 --> 00:08:58.430
Hey! Stop inviting people onto our ship!

134
00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:03.480
Hey!

135
00:09:03.480 --> 00:09:05.110
Bonney!

136
00:09:05.110 --> 00:09:07.230
Old Man Punk!

137
00:09:07.230 --> 00:09:08.740
Where are you?!

138
00:09:08.740 --> 00:09:10.450
Luffy!

139
00:09:10.950 --> 00:09:12.160
Chopper!

140
00:09:12.160 --> 00:09:13.280
Did you find them?

141
00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:15.620
I don't see them anywhere.

142
00:09:15.620 --> 00:09:19.250
That's weird! Where are they?

143
00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:21.250
I'm gonna go check down there!

144
00:09:21.250 --> 00:09:22.330
Thanks!

145
00:09:21.790 --> 00:09:22.330
Yeah!

146
00:09:23.210 --> 00:09:25.210
Oh boy...

147
00:09:25.210 --> 00:09:26.300
Hey!

148
00:09:26.800 --> 00:09:30.630
Old man! We can't set sail if you're gone!

149
00:09:32.890 --> 00:09:38.850
Saving Bonney led the Straw Hats
to Future Island, Egghead.

150
00:09:39.640 --> 00:09:42.350
But an incident occurred.

151
00:09:43.350 --> 00:09:45.900
Old man!

152
00:09:48.480 --> 00:09:53.240
Dr. Vegapunk Stella has disappeared!

153
00:09:54.780 --> 00:09:58.410
This is Sphinx, in the New World.

154
00:09:58.990 --> 00:10:02.040
The pirate Whitebeard's hometown.

155
00:10:06.920 --> 00:10:10.420
Hey, Marco! You missed
something really scary!

156
00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:12.760
I wasn't scared though!

157
00:10:13.090 --> 00:10:15.890
The Marines showed up all of a sudden!

158
00:10:15.890 --> 00:10:17.930
I'm really sorry...

159
00:10:17.930 --> 00:10:21.890
I can only imagine how scared you were.

160
00:10:21.890 --> 00:10:24.150
I was not scared!

161
00:10:24.150 --> 00:10:26.480
Then what happened?

162
00:10:26.480 --> 00:10:27.610
Listen, listen!

163
00:10:27.610 --> 00:10:30.190
The Marines were horrible!

164
00:10:30.190 --> 00:10:33.280
They said they were gonna
steal Whitebeard's treasure!

165
00:10:33.280 --> 00:10:35.530
They acted just like pirates!

166
00:10:33.280 --> 00:10:35.740
<b>Several Days Ago</b>

167
00:11:01.850 --> 00:11:04.480
Gather all the villagers.

168
00:11:04.480 --> 00:11:05.350
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

169
00:11:10.520 --> 00:11:14.490
Do as we say and no one gets hurt.

170
00:11:14.490 --> 00:11:18.370
This island is not affiliated
with the World Government!

171
00:11:18.370 --> 00:11:20.950
You people aren't protected by the law!

172
00:11:21.410 --> 00:11:25.460
I believe Whitebeard's vast treasure
is somewhere on the island.

173
00:11:25.790 --> 00:11:27.670
Tell me where it is!

174
00:11:28.170 --> 00:11:32.130
E-Even if you threaten us,
we've never heard of any treasure!

175
00:11:32.760 --> 00:11:35.090
Oh...

176
00:11:35.090 --> 00:11:37.340
Is that so...?

177
00:11:40.800 --> 00:11:42.310
R-Really, we–

178
00:11:42.310 --> 00:11:45.020
If you don't tell us...

179
00:11:45.020 --> 00:11:48.230
we'll consider it an act of rebellion!

180
00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:51.570
Or maybe...

181
00:11:53.530 --> 00:11:55.740
if I shoot you all one by one,

182
00:11:56.110 --> 00:11:58.070
you'll tell me after all?

183
00:12:00.070 --> 00:12:02.160
Th-There is no such thing!

184
00:12:02.160 --> 00:12:04.540
Don't point a gun at my little brother!

185
00:12:04.540 --> 00:12:09.000
So if we can't pay the government,
you won't even treat us like humans?!

186
00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:11.630
You brutes!

187
00:12:11.630 --> 00:12:12.960
Aren't you scared?

188
00:12:12.960 --> 00:12:16.420
Marco isn't here to protect you now.

189
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:18.970
Restrain her.

190
00:12:19.760 --> 00:12:21.720
What are you doing?!

191
00:12:21.720 --> 00:12:23.310
Grandma!

192
00:12:23.310 --> 00:12:24.430
Stop it!

193
00:12:24.430 --> 00:12:26.310
I said stop!

194
00:12:27.560 --> 00:12:29.060
Don't do it!

195
00:12:29.060 --> 00:12:30.230
She's one of our elders!

196
00:12:30.230 --> 00:12:32.270
Grandma!

197
00:12:33.860 --> 00:12:34.860
No!

198
00:12:34.860 --> 00:12:36.190
Let go of me!

199
00:13:03.010 --> 00:13:05.850
Don't mess with...

200
00:13:05.850 --> 00:13:09.640
my daddy's hometown!

201
00:13:09.640 --> 00:13:12.100
It's Edward Weevil!

202
00:13:12.860 --> 00:13:14.360
W-We gotta run!

203
00:13:14.360 --> 00:13:15.110
Yeah!

204
00:13:15.110 --> 00:13:16.570
H-Hey!

205
00:13:17.150 --> 00:13:21.700
I thought they sent ships after him
when the Warlords were disbanded!

206
00:13:21.700 --> 00:13:23.910
But we lost contact with them!

207
00:13:23.910 --> 00:13:26.240
They must've been beaten! All of them!

208
00:13:26.240 --> 00:13:28.830
His strength really is monstrous!

209
00:13:28.830 --> 00:13:31.710
Retreat to the ship!
We'll wait for reinforcements!

210
00:13:32.370 --> 00:13:34.130
This is Sphinx!

211
00:13:34.130 --> 00:13:36.670
The ex-Warlord Weevil showed up!

212
00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:39.260
We need backup!

213
00:13:40.130 --> 00:13:44.090
And then the Marines that were
invading the village ran away!

214
00:13:45.550 --> 00:13:49.770
If that big guy hadn't shown up,
we would've been done for!

215
00:13:51.140 --> 00:13:53.150
Guess he's a hero, then.

216
00:13:53.150 --> 00:13:55.150
I'm really glad that you're all okay.

217
00:13:55.150 --> 00:13:57.610
Hold it, Marco!

218
00:13:58.070 --> 00:14:00.360
Who do you think they sent in after that?!

219
00:14:01.240 --> 00:14:04.410
Marine Admiral Ryokugyu showed up...

220
00:14:05.160 --> 00:14:08.910
and took my Weevil away,
kicking and screaming!

221
00:14:08.910 --> 00:14:10.750
Weevil!

222
00:14:10.750 --> 00:14:13.670
Mommy!

223
00:14:15.130 --> 00:14:17.130
Give me back my son!

224
00:14:17.130 --> 00:14:18.210
And...

225
00:14:18.250 --> 00:14:24.050
<b>......................</b>
<b>Miss Buckin
Freeloader at MADS
Self-Proclaimed Scientist
Ex-Rocks Pirates Member</b>
<b>......................................</b>
<b>..............................................</b>
<b>...............................................</b>

226
00:14:19.710 --> 00:14:24.050
give us Edward "Whitebeard"
Newgate's heritage!

227
00:14:24.050 --> 00:14:27.850
<b>Real Name:
Buckingham Stussy</b>
<b>............................</b>
<b>.................................................</b>

228
00:14:30.430 --> 00:14:35.100
Sent to jail for protecting his
father's village! Such a brave boy!

229
00:14:35.730 --> 00:14:39.610
That's our boy...!

230
00:14:42.570 --> 00:14:46.910
I'm truly grateful he protected the village...

231
00:14:48.700 --> 00:14:49.910
Marco!

232
00:14:49.910 --> 00:14:54.080
You don't believe that Weevil is
Whitebeard's son either, do you?!

233
00:14:55.420 --> 00:14:58.710
Well, I know someone who can prove it!

234
00:14:59.420 --> 00:15:01.510
Dr. Vegapunk!

235
00:15:11.430 --> 00:15:12.560
Kizaru, sir!

236
00:15:12.560 --> 00:15:15.520
We brought some tea and snacks.

237
00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:18.310
And you've tested them for poison?

238
00:15:18.310 --> 00:15:19.520
Of course!

239
00:15:19.520 --> 00:15:22.190
I'll take them. You can go.

240
00:15:22.190 --> 00:15:22.990
Yes, sir!

241
00:15:35.870 --> 00:15:37.830
May I come in?

242
00:15:39.210 --> 00:15:41.840
I brought you a little something...

243
00:15:42.460 --> 00:15:44.340
Please, help yourself.

244
00:15:50.930 --> 00:15:56.390
Have you ever met Dr. Vegapunk before?

245
00:16:04.070 --> 00:16:06.860
Just once, a long time ago.

246
00:16:07.400 --> 00:16:09.740
I can't believe...

247
00:16:09.740 --> 00:16:12.530
he would betray you.

248
00:16:19.460 --> 00:16:23.380
<b>St. Jaygarcia Saturn
The Five Elders, Supreme Council of the World Government</b>

249
00:16:23.380 --> 00:16:28.550
Truly, what has happened is most regrettable.

250
00:16:31.600 --> 00:16:32.680
Is that...

251
00:16:34.680 --> 00:16:36.850
<b>Fabriophase
Egghead</b>

252
00:16:43.020 --> 00:16:44.230
A pacifista?!

253
00:16:44.230 --> 00:16:46.860
Wait! You're with the Marines, right?

254
00:16:46.860 --> 00:16:50.280
You're supposed to be on our side.
Don't get in our way!

255
00:16:51.410 --> 00:16:53.740
Hey! What are you doing?!

256
00:17:06.460 --> 00:17:08.170
How dare you attack your own!

257
00:17:11.680 --> 00:17:12.840
Is that...?

258
00:17:12.840 --> 00:17:14.390
Stop! Don't shoot!

259
00:17:30.110 --> 00:17:31.950
What kind of ability is that?!

260
00:17:31.950 --> 00:17:34.120
That's a bubble shield!

261
00:17:34.120 --> 00:17:38.580
So this is the ultimate shield
that Vegapunk invented.

262
00:17:38.580 --> 00:17:42.330
This version far surpasses the prototypes
used in the Summit War...

263
00:17:42.330 --> 00:17:44.790
Pacifista Mk. III!

264
00:17:56.850 --> 00:17:59.810
<b>y432lumoctvBNOG
S29wu,8jF0RQDUb</b>
<b>0UKVbdqBJCgONNL
sLcWKaSjD;F8r!l</b>
<b>Combat Weapon of Marines' Science Group</b>
Do not resist. Proceed to Factory Building B.

265
00:18:03.350 --> 00:18:06.150
Confirmed hostile activity.

266
00:18:08.690 --> 00:18:11.190
We'll all die if we don't surrender!

267
00:18:11.700 --> 00:18:13.410
Hurry up!

268
00:18:20.080 --> 00:18:22.040
Initiating capture.

269
00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:26.790
Why?!

270
00:18:27.170 --> 00:18:30.010
The pacifista shouldn't act on their own!

271
00:18:30.010 --> 00:18:32.050
Who's giving it orders?!

272
00:18:30.630 --> 00:18:36.260
<b>Fabrio</b>

273
00:18:38.140 --> 00:18:39.260
Don't move!

274
00:18:39.260 --> 00:18:40.770
It's bad for your wounds.

275
00:18:43.480 --> 00:18:45.480
So much for my day off...

276
00:18:45.480 --> 00:18:48.610
Are the pacifista performing well?

277
00:18:51.490 --> 00:18:53.320
Something's going on up there.

278
00:18:53.820 --> 00:18:56.070
This is Sentomaru. Respond!

279
00:18:58.030 --> 00:18:59.990
Hey! Old Man Punk!

280
00:19:01.910 --> 00:19:03.410
No response.

281
00:19:03.410 --> 00:19:05.420
And the Frontier Dome is closed.

282
00:19:06.040 --> 00:19:09.170
I can't reach Old Man Punk...

283
00:19:09.710 --> 00:19:12.920
I trust you with Old Man Punk!

284
00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:14.840
Alright!

285
00:19:14.840 --> 00:19:16.260
Leave it to me!

286
00:19:19.100 --> 00:19:23.230
What's concerning is that the Marines
are continuously communicating...

287
00:19:23.230 --> 00:19:25.310
but we've been cut out of the loop.

288
00:19:28.980 --> 00:19:30.730
Old Man Punk...

289
00:19:30.730 --> 00:19:32.440
I'm a traitor too, now.

290
00:19:36.150 --> 00:19:38.870
So I guess I'll do what I want.

291
00:19:39.450 --> 00:19:41.030
Pacifista Mk. III!

292
00:19:41.030 --> 00:19:42.490
Activate!

293
00:19:52.710 --> 00:19:54.920
All fifty of you, go!

294
00:19:59.640 --> 00:20:03.850
Straw Hat Luffy is taking
Dr. Vegapunk aboard his ship!

295
00:20:03.850 --> 00:20:06.940
Your mission is to ensure its safe departure!

296
00:20:06.940 --> 00:20:08.560
– Roger.
– Roger.

297
00:20:12.730 --> 00:20:15.070
The Marines are acting strange!

298
00:20:15.990 --> 00:20:17.490
Watch the shore!

299
00:20:17.490 --> 00:20:20.030
Something is about to happen here...

300
00:20:21.200 --> 00:20:24.620
Make sure your creator...

301
00:20:24.620 --> 00:20:27.460
makes it off this island!

302
00:20:28.960 --> 00:20:33.380
<b>The P.A.W. Room
Inside the Lab</b>

303
00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:33.380
Stop! Don't touch it!

304
00:20:33.380 --> 00:20:34.380
Shut up!

305
00:20:34.380 --> 00:20:35.590
Get out!

306
00:20:37.340 --> 00:20:40.430
Bonney!

307
00:21:35.150 --> 00:21:36.610
What's the matter?

308
00:21:36.610 --> 00:21:37.900
Hey...

309
00:21:37.900 --> 00:21:39.650
What happened?

310
00:21:41.950 --> 00:21:44.780
I can't take it anymore...

311
00:21:44.780 --> 00:21:46.620
I really can't...

312
00:21:49.080 --> 00:21:51.210
Dad?

313
00:21:51.210 --> 00:21:53.120
There he is!

314
00:22:01.260 --> 00:22:02.970
Don't try to run!

315
00:22:02.970 --> 00:22:04.720
Stop messing around!

316
00:22:04.720 --> 00:22:05.600
C'mon!

317
00:22:05.600 --> 00:22:07.010
No!

318
00:22:07.010 --> 00:22:08.100
I don't want to!

319
00:22:08.520 --> 00:22:09.640
Shut up!

320
00:22:09.640 --> 00:22:11.060
Just come with us!

321
00:22:15.560 --> 00:22:17.360
No! Let go of me!

322
00:22:17.730 --> 00:22:19.900
Please! Let go of me!

323
00:22:19.900 --> 00:22:21.240
Help!

324
00:22:21.240 --> 00:22:22.900
I can't take it anymore!

325
00:22:22.900 --> 00:22:24.160
You little punk!

326
00:22:24.160 --> 00:22:25.700
You gotta go back now!

327
00:22:25.700 --> 00:22:29.700
If you run, we'll all get killed!

328
00:22:29.700 --> 00:22:32.710
But... But I don't wanna go back...

329
00:22:32.710 --> 00:22:34.330
I don't wanna go back!

330
00:22:34.330 --> 00:22:36.290
Help!

331
00:22:36.290 --> 00:22:38.670
I can't take it anymore!

332
00:22:37.540 --> 00:22:38.670
Come on already!

333
00:22:38.670 --> 00:22:42.760
Help me!

334
00:22:43.380 --> 00:22:45.890
Stop it!

335
00:22:45.890 --> 00:22:47.140
No!

336
00:22:47.140 --> 00:22:49.350
I don't ever wanna go back there!

337
00:22:51.730 --> 00:22:52.850
Stop it!

338
00:22:52.850 --> 00:22:54.190
He doesn't want to!

339
00:22:57.810 --> 00:22:59.070
What?

340
00:23:01.820 --> 00:23:03.240
I can't get any closer...

341
00:23:07.660 --> 00:23:08.950
Crying won't do any good!

342
00:23:08.950 --> 00:23:10.490
Shitty kid!

343
00:23:13.160 --> 00:23:16.290
No... I can't take it anymore...

344
00:23:16.290 --> 00:23:18.040
Stop resisting!

345
00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:18.790
Go back!

346
00:23:18.790 --> 00:23:19.670
No!

347
00:23:19.670 --> 00:23:20.550
You little shit!

348
00:23:20.550 --> 00:23:21.800
I'm not going back!

349
00:23:21.170 --> 00:23:21.800
Hey!

350
00:23:22.210 --> 00:23:24.420
Just kill me right here!

351
00:23:24.420 --> 00:23:25.760
Even if I go back...

352
00:23:25.760 --> 00:23:29.010
I'm just gonna die anyway!

353
00:23:29.350 --> 00:23:30.430
What?

354
00:23:30.430 --> 00:23:32.640
Shut up!

355
00:23:35.060 --> 00:23:38.150
Stop!

356
00:23:53.700 --> 00:23:55.500
Stop!

357
00:23:55.500 --> 00:23:56.580
I said stop!

358
00:23:57.580 --> 00:24:00.750
Stop it!

359
00:24:03.710 --> 00:24:04.840
It hurts...

360
00:24:06.680 --> 00:24:07.880
I'm sorry!

361
00:24:08.340 --> 00:24:10.970
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

362
00:24:12.930 --> 00:24:15.310
Stop! Stop!

363
00:24:17.440 --> 00:24:20.440
It hurts... I'm sorry...

364
00:24:20.440 --> 00:24:23.820
Just kill me...

365
00:24:27.070 --> 00:24:27.740
Stop...

366
00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:31.830
Please... just stop...

367
00:24:33.830 --> 00:24:35.540
Help!

368
00:24:35.540 --> 00:24:38.870
Help!

369
00:24:37.410 --> 00:24:38.370
Stop...

370
00:24:39.250 --> 00:24:41.840
Please stop...

371
00:24:42.460 --> 00:24:44.500
Stop it now!

372
00:25:02.400 --> 00:25:03.900
Shoot him down!

373
00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:18.500
Bartholomew Kuma is climbing the Red Line,
seemingly headed for Mary Geoise!

374
00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:21.790
Do not allow him to enter Mary Geoise!

375
00:25:22.290 --> 00:25:26.500
The reputation of the Marines is at stake!

376
00:25:33.800 --> 00:25:35.760
Dad's past...

377
00:25:36.470 --> 00:25:38.350
I don't think I can face this...

378
00:25:40.190 --> 00:25:42.150
unless I'm actually ready for it.

379
00:25:46.730 --> 00:25:48.110
But...

380
00:25:50.490 --> 00:25:53.110
I can't accept all this until I know the truth!

381
00:25:54.950 --> 00:25:56.200
Hey...

382
00:25:56.200 --> 00:25:57.540
Dad.

383
00:26:01.120 --> 00:26:04.380
Show it to me one more time.

384
00:26:11.170 --> 00:26:12.510
What?!

385
00:26:11.220 --> 00:26:15.640
<b>Labophase
Egghead</b>

386
00:26:12.510 --> 00:26:15.640
What do you mean Vegapunk
is missing? Where did he go?!

387
00:26:15.640 --> 00:26:19.100
Did you look everywhere?
He must be here in the lab, right?

388
00:26:22.350 --> 00:26:24.690
Well, I mean...

389
00:26:24.690 --> 00:26:27.940
I ran all over the place...

390
00:26:30.070 --> 00:26:32.280
But I couldn't find him.

391
00:26:32.280 --> 00:26:33.570
Did you really?

392
00:26:33.570 --> 00:26:34.910
Yes, he did!

393
00:26:34.910 --> 00:26:38.120
His hover boots broke,
so he was running the whole time!

394
00:26:38.120 --> 00:26:39.540
Don't tell them that!

395
00:26:39.540 --> 00:26:41.330
I can't pay for them!

396
00:26:41.330 --> 00:26:44.290
This is not the time for that!

397
00:26:44.290 --> 00:26:46.840
Where did Vegapunk go?!

398
00:26:46.840 --> 00:26:48.500
Usopp, relax.

399
00:26:48.500 --> 00:26:50.760
How can I relax?!

400
00:26:50.760 --> 00:26:53.970
We gotta go soon or we'll have
to face another one of those monsters!

401
00:26:54.380 --> 00:26:56.590
I guess we can't set off yet.

402
00:26:57.800 --> 00:27:00.680
Where did apple gramps go?

403
00:27:00.680 --> 00:27:01.930
Or Bonney...

404
00:27:02.310 --> 00:27:04.190
I wonder if she's okay.

405
00:27:04.190 --> 00:27:06.020
Actually, Bonney's right here.

406
00:27:06.020 --> 00:27:06.690
– What?
– What?

407
00:27:07.190 --> 00:27:09.570
This monitor shows everything in the lab.

408
00:27:09.570 --> 00:27:10.940
Why didn't you say so?

409
00:27:10.940 --> 00:27:11.690
She never left.

410
00:27:11.690 --> 00:27:12.740
– Then say so!
– Then say so!

411
00:27:14.990 --> 00:27:15.700
Hey.

412
00:27:15.700 --> 00:27:17.070
Sheesh...

413
00:27:17.660 --> 00:27:18.910
Zoro!

414
00:27:18.910 --> 00:27:20.370
What's taking you so long?

415
00:27:20.740 --> 00:27:22.580
Aren't we about to sail?

416
00:27:22.580 --> 00:27:24.540
We've got a few issues!

417
00:27:24.540 --> 00:27:28.170
Still, this place sure is something else!

418
00:27:28.170 --> 00:27:30.300
The future is amazing!

419
00:27:30.300 --> 00:27:31.800
The future is amazing!

420
00:27:31.800 --> 00:27:34.920
There's even a hat that fits you, Brook!

421
00:27:34.920 --> 00:27:37.720
Is that what you call futuristic?

422
00:27:38.340 --> 00:27:41.350
This place is in worse shape than I thought.

423
00:27:41.350 --> 00:27:44.100
Shaka, how's Atlas?

424
00:27:44.850 --> 00:27:45.560
Edison.

425
00:27:45.560 --> 00:27:46.690
Lilith.

426
00:27:46.690 --> 00:27:48.650
Don't go bossing us around, Shaka!

427
00:27:48.650 --> 00:27:50.150
'Scuse me!

428
00:27:50.150 --> 00:27:51.940
Repairs are all done!

429
00:27:51.940 --> 00:27:53.070
Come have a look!

430
00:27:53.070 --> 00:27:55.780
Don't act like you did all the work!

431
00:27:55.780 --> 00:27:57.700
I fixed her up with you!

432
00:27:59.870 --> 00:28:02.330
Sup! Sorry for the wait!

433
00:28:02.330 --> 00:28:06.210
I'm back and ready to go!

434
00:28:07.420 --> 00:28:08.670
Knock it off, would ya?!

435
00:28:11.210 --> 00:28:13.590
I feel great!

436
00:28:13.590 --> 00:28:14.920
Alright, alright!

437
00:28:14.920 --> 00:28:17.090
Sure are lively now that you're all fixed up...

438
00:28:17.090 --> 00:28:18.510
What a handful!

439
00:28:25.100 --> 00:28:26.730
Good morning, Atlas.

440
00:28:26.730 --> 00:28:27.520
Yo!

441
00:28:27.520 --> 00:28:28.810
Were you asleep again?

442
00:28:28.810 --> 00:28:30.480
How long have you been sleeping?

443
00:28:30.480 --> 00:28:33.270
Want me to really wake you up?

444
00:28:34.480 --> 00:28:36.110
There's no need for that!

445
00:28:39.160 --> 00:28:41.530
You repaired her face?

446
00:28:42.030 --> 00:28:44.040
We have replacement parts.

447
00:28:44.870 --> 00:28:46.250
It's you!

448
00:28:46.250 --> 00:28:48.370
You saved my life, didn't you?!

449
00:28:48.370 --> 00:28:49.330
Thanks!

450
00:28:49.330 --> 00:28:50.500
Yeah!

451
00:28:51.750 --> 00:28:54.090
How dare they hurt such a cute girl!

452
00:28:54.460 --> 00:28:57.920
These jerks haven't changed
since Water Seven!

453
00:28:57.920 --> 00:29:02.100
If you're here for Robin again,
I'll kick your asses myself!

454
00:29:02.850 --> 00:29:04.060
Nami...

455
00:29:04.060 --> 00:29:06.220
They're not a threat right now.

456
00:29:06.560 --> 00:29:10.650
Now then, I came to see
Stella. What happened?

457
00:29:10.650 --> 00:29:13.110
We have a couple of mysteries.

458
00:29:13.110 --> 00:29:14.730
Please don't be alarmed.

459
00:29:14.730 --> 00:29:15.480
First:

460
00:29:16.030 --> 00:29:17.690
Stella is missing.

461
00:29:17.690 --> 00:29:19.360
And second:

462
00:29:19.360 --> 00:29:21.950
We have lost control of the Frontier Dome.

463
00:29:21.950 --> 00:29:22.660
What?

464
00:29:22.660 --> 00:29:24.240
What do you mean?

465
00:29:25.620 --> 00:29:30.210
It means we can no longer
get out of the Labophase.

466
00:29:31.540 --> 00:29:35.880
If you try to leave the perimeter,
you'll be shot to death by lasers.

467
00:29:35.880 --> 00:29:37.050
Hold on a sec!

468
00:29:37.050 --> 00:29:40.090
But we're supposed to be
leaving with Vegapunk, right?!

469
00:29:40.090 --> 00:29:43.340
Yes, but the man himself isn't here.

470
00:29:43.340 --> 00:29:45.310
What should we do?!

471
00:29:45.810 --> 00:29:49.310
You can help by finding Stella.

472
00:29:49.310 --> 00:29:51.690
I'll try to fix the dome somehow.

473
00:29:52.060 --> 00:29:56.820
But if the monitor is showing
everything except for him,

474
00:29:56.820 --> 00:29:59.190
why should we bother looking for him?

475
00:29:59.190 --> 00:30:02.950
Normally, it shows everything in the lab,

476
00:30:02.950 --> 00:30:05.580
but due to the shock of the seraphim's attack,

477
00:30:05.580 --> 00:30:09.410
the camsnails have either left
their posts or passed out.

478
00:30:10.040 --> 00:30:14.790
I've been having the satellites and
lab workers inspect those areas themselves.

479
00:30:14.790 --> 00:30:18.170
He might have collapsed in a blind spot.

480
00:30:18.170 --> 00:30:20.510
Shaka. This is Pythagoras.

481
00:30:20.840 --> 00:30:23.470
I didn't find anyone on Building C's third floor.

482
00:30:23.890 --> 00:30:25.010
Understood.

483
00:30:25.010 --> 00:30:27.720
Check the next building over as well.

484
00:30:27.720 --> 00:30:29.770
We should go look for him too.

485
00:30:29.770 --> 00:30:31.890
Let's find him and get out of here.

486
00:30:32.230 --> 00:30:34.600
I wanna find the treasure of the future too!

487
00:30:34.600 --> 00:30:36.360
Oh, that sounds like fun.

488
00:30:36.360 --> 00:30:37.610
I'll come with you!

489
00:30:37.610 --> 00:30:38.860
Hold on just one minute!

490
00:30:38.860 --> 00:30:41.440
You guys ain't up to no good, are you?!

491
00:30:41.440 --> 00:30:43.950
Of course not. Right, Nami?

492
00:30:43.950 --> 00:30:45.070
Who knows?

493
00:30:45.070 --> 00:30:48.080
See?! You are up to something!

494
00:30:48.080 --> 00:30:49.830
I'll go look too.

495
00:30:49.830 --> 00:30:51.830
His disappearance is making me uneasy.

496
00:30:51.830 --> 00:30:53.710
I'll come with you.

497
00:30:53.710 --> 00:30:55.290
Oh, thank you.

498
00:30:56.670 --> 00:30:58.250
Mistress Stussy!

499
00:30:58.630 --> 00:31:00.710
Take me with you too!

500
00:31:01.090 --> 00:31:02.300
I have no choice.

501
00:31:02.300 --> 00:31:04.300
I guess I'll go look too.

502
00:31:04.300 --> 00:31:05.260
Hold it, Moss Head!

503
00:31:05.260 --> 00:31:06.680
What do you want?

504
00:31:06.680 --> 00:31:09.510
I just gotta find an old guy
with his head cut off, right?

505
00:31:09.510 --> 00:31:10.260
You?!

506
00:31:10.770 --> 00:31:11.520
Looking for...

507
00:31:11.890 --> 00:31:13.180
someone else?!

508
00:31:13.180 --> 00:31:15.480
Shut up! Let go of me, shitty cook!

509
00:31:15.480 --> 00:31:16.980
If you do that...

510
00:31:16.980 --> 00:31:18.770
who's gonna look for you?

511
00:31:18.770 --> 00:31:19.820
That's...!

512
00:31:19.820 --> 00:31:21.440
He's right, Zoro!

513
00:31:21.440 --> 00:31:22.570
You should stay here!

514
00:31:22.570 --> 00:31:23.570
You too?!

515
00:31:23.570 --> 00:31:25.950
Please wait here patiently.

516
00:31:25.950 --> 00:31:27.410
Whatever...

517
00:31:27.410 --> 00:31:29.700
Wait for me, Vegapunk!

518
00:31:29.700 --> 00:31:31.410
Now, where should we check first?!

519
00:31:31.410 --> 00:31:32.910
I don't know!

520
00:31:32.910 --> 00:31:34.910
Those hallways are like a maze!

521
00:31:34.910 --> 00:31:37.420
We're definitely gonna get lost.

522
00:31:37.420 --> 00:31:40.380
Pirates sure are a handful.

523
00:31:40.380 --> 00:31:41.550
Just follow my lead!

524
00:31:41.550 --> 00:31:43.630
Sure! That'd be great!

525
00:31:44.260 --> 00:31:45.470
Are you sleeping again?

526
00:31:45.470 --> 00:31:48.180
You sleep too much. Let's go.

527
00:31:51.560 --> 00:31:53.140
Okay...

528
00:31:57.940 --> 00:32:01.520
Man, I really don't know what
they were talking about...

529
00:32:02.980 --> 00:32:05.450
Well, I guess even they can find one person.

530
00:32:06.200 --> 00:32:08.160
I can't believe you ran full blast.

531
00:32:09.780 --> 00:32:13.660
I always do things... full blast...!

532
00:32:13.660 --> 00:32:15.580
Well, anyway...

533
00:32:15.580 --> 00:32:18.790
I never thought we'd see these guys again.

534
00:32:19.290 --> 00:32:22.000
It takes me back to Water Seven.

535
00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:25.590
I hope Iceboss is doing alright.

536
00:32:31.930 --> 00:32:35.140
Check it out! I got a big scoop!

537
00:32:35.520 --> 00:32:40.560
The World Government is carrying out 
the assassination of the famous Dr. Vegapunk!

538
00:32:40.560 --> 00:32:43.320
Assassinating the world's brightest mind?!

539
00:32:43.650 --> 00:32:46.360
This is the Ohara incident all over again!

540
00:32:46.360 --> 00:32:48.990
But the government's odds aren't good!

541
00:32:48.990 --> 00:32:51.200
Vegapunk is a worldwide sensation.

542
00:32:51.200 --> 00:32:56.160
He lit up the world with his
marvelous energy technology!

543
00:32:56.160 --> 00:32:58.080
And who just so happens to be there...

544
00:32:58.080 --> 00:33:00.540
but this guy?!

545
00:33:01.420 --> 00:33:08.260
